missing_requirements.description: No throughput capacity requirement for WaterRecyclingSubsystem to ensure sufficient daily water production.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: REQ-XXX: The WaterRecyclingSubsystem shall process a minimum of 1,000 liters per day under peak operating conditions to meet water demand of occupants.
missing_requirements.rationale: Without a defined throughput capacity, the subsystem may under-produce water, risking insufficient potable water supply for occupants.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for backup power mechanism in WaterRecyclingSubsystem for handling power failures.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: REQ-XXX: The WaterRecyclingSubsystem shall include a backup power mechanism (e.g., UPS or generator) to ensure continuous operation during power failures.
missing_requirements.rationale: The system must operate continuously 24×7, but there's no requirement addressing power failure scenarios for the WaterRecyclingSubsystem.

missing_requirements.description: No requirement to monitor water storage levels and alert when tanks are low.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: REQ-XXX: The WaterStorageSubsystem shall monitor water levels for potable, black, and gray water tanks and generate alerts when any tank level falls below 20% of its capacity.
missing_requirements.rationale: Alerts on low storage levels are critical to schedule replenishment and avoid service interruption.

missing_requirements.description: No requirement for monitoring device to alert occupants when water quality falls below safety standards.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: REQ-XXX: The MonitoringDevice shall alert occupants when water quality parameters fall outside safety standards defined by regulatory bodies.
missing_requirements.rationale: The domain model shows a MonitoringDevice that communicates water quality, but there's no explicit requirement for alerting occupants when safety standards are not met, which is critical for health and safety.

missing_requirements.description: No requirement for redundant monitoring devices in water subsystems to ensure failover.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: REQ-XXX: The WaterRecyclingSubsystem and WaterStorageSubsystem shall each include a redundant MonitoringDevice to ensure continuous monitoring in case of primary device failure.
missing_requirements.rationale: Redundancy prevents loss of monitoring capability and undetected failures.

missing_requirements.description: No requirement for automatic activation and continuous monitoring of the fire suppression system upon fire detection.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: REQ-XXX: The FireSuppressionSystem shall automatically activate within 30 seconds of fire detection by the MonitoringDevice, continuously monitor its status, and generate immediate alerts if activation fails.
missing_requirements.rationale: Automatic activation reduces response time and occupant risk, and monitoring prevents undetected failures in a safety-critical system.

missing_requirements.description: DedicatedApplication lacks requirements for user authentication, UI presentation, data export functionality, and secure access control.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: REQ-XXX: The DedicatedApplication shall implement user authentication, present real-time monitoring data via graphical dashboard, provide system control capabilities, configurable alert thresholds, and allow data export to CSV and PDF formats, accessible via web browser and mobile devices.
missing_requirements.rationale: A secure and user-friendly interface with comprehensive functionality is essential for effective system monitoring, control, and analysis.

missing_requirements.description: IceCoreStorage does not specify inventory management, handling, contamination prevention, sample tracking, and temperature monitoring.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: REQ-XXX: The IceCoreStorage subsystem shall maintain a digital inventory with sample ID, location, chain-of-custody tracking, environmental condition logging, contamination prevention procedures, and integrate with the Database; it shall include temperature sensors that alert when temperatures fall outside -40°F to 20°F.
missing_requirements.rationale: Comprehensive sample management and condition monitoring ensure ice core integrity, compliance with research protocols, and data traceability.

missing_requirements.description: Sensors lack specifications for accuracy, self-diagnostics, calibration, timestamping, and environmental operating ranges.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: REQ-XXX: All Sensor devices shall meet ±2% accuracy, provide digital output with timestamp, perform self-diagnostics and calibration checks at least every 24 hours with monthly automated calibration procedures, record calibration history, and operate reliably in -40°F to 100°F and 10% to 90% humidity.
missing_requirements.rationale: Defining sensor performance and maintenance requirements is essential for accurate measurements and reliable system operation.

missing_requirements.description: No system availability or reliability targets defined for critical life support functions.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: REQ-XXX: The facility shall achieve at least 99.9% availability for critical life support functions (power, heating, water, waste processing, fire suppression) over any 30-day period.
missing_requirements.rationale: Availability targets are essential to ensure continuous operation and occupant safety.

missing_requirements.description: No requirements for data backup, retention, encryption, integrity verification, and recovery procedures for the facility's Database and cloud storage.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: REQ-XXX: The Database and CloudStorage shall perform automated daily backups with encrypted storage, retain backups for at least one year, conduct integrity checks, and enable disaster recovery to restore critical systems within four hours.
missing_requirements.rationale: Comprehensive backup and recovery procedures protect against data loss, ensure mission continuity, and support recovery after failures.

missing_requirements.description: ControlSystem lacks role-based access control, multi-factor authentication, session management, and auditing of user actions.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: REQ-XXX: The ControlSystem and SmartDevice interfaces shall implement role-based access control with individual user accounts, multi-factor authentication for privileged operations, session timeout after 15 minutes of inactivity, and audit logging of all user actions.
missing_requirements.rationale: Enhanced access controls and auditing are required to secure critical facility functions and data against unauthorized use.

missing_requirements.description: No provision for manual override and emergency shutdown of critical life support functions in the event of automated control or power failures.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: REQ-XXX: The ControlSystem shall provide manual mechanical or hardware overrides and an emergency shutdown feature accessible within the facility for all critical life support systems (power generation, heating, water filtration, fire suppression).
missing_requirements.rationale: Manual overrides and emergency shutdown capabilities are essential for maintaining safety when automated controls or power are unavailable.

missing_requirements.description: No requirement for interior environmental condition monitoring including temperature, humidity, CO₂, CO, and other harmful gases.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: REQ-XXX: The facility shall monitor interior temperature (65°F–75°F), relative humidity (30%–60%), CO₂, CO, and other harmful gas levels, generating alerts for any out-of-range conditions.
missing_requirements.rationale: Monitoring ambient conditions ensures occupant comfort, health, and equipment reliability.

missing_requirements.description: FuelStorage lacks secondary containment and leak detection sensor requirements to prevent environmental contamination.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: REQ-XXX: FuelStorage tanks shall include secondary containment capable of holding 110% of the largest tank volume and leak-detection sensors that alert operators upon detection of a spill.
missing_requirements.rationale: Secondary containment and leak detection are required to comply with SPCC regulations and prevent environmental contamination.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for monitoring fuel levels in FuelStorage and low-level alerts.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: REQ-XXX: The FuelStorage subsystem shall include a monitoring device that alerts the facility when fuel levels fall below a predefined threshold.
missing_requirements.rationale: Fuel is critical for power generation, and low fuel levels must be detected to prevent unexpected power loss.

missing_requirements.description: No automated inventory tracking and resupply alert requirements for consumables including food, medical supplies, filters, and fuel.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: REQ-XXX: The facility shall maintain automated inventory tracking for all consumables with minimum stock level alerts set at two-week consumption rates, generating weekly reports for resupply planning.
missing_requirements.rationale: Given the remote location and limited resupply, automated inventory management is critical for mission sustainability.

missing_requirements.description: RefrigerationSystem and FreezerSystem lack temperature monitoring, alarm requirements, and ability to maintain setpoints under extreme weather conditions.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: REQ-XXX: Both RefrigerationSystem and FreezerSystem shall continuously monitor internal temperatures (refrigeration: 34°F–40°F; freezer: –20°F±2°F), maintain setpoints under external conditions ranging from –40°F to 80°F, and generate alarms for any deviations.
missing_requirements.rationale: Temperature monitoring, alarms, and environmental resilience protect perishables and scientific samples.

missing_requirements.description: No requirement for redundant communication paths, emergency beacon, GPS, and automatic failover between primary and backup links.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: REQ-XXX: The facility shall support at least two independent communication paths (e.g., radio, satellite) and an emergency beacon with GPS, automatically switching to a backup within 30 seconds; all communication equipment shall undergo weekly functionality tests.
missing_requirements.rationale: Redundant communications and testing ensure mission-critical data exchange and emergency signaling under adverse conditions.

missing_requirements.description: No requirement for integration with external Power Generation Subsystem (PGS) for power allocation and status monitoring.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: REQ-XXX: The facility shall communicate with the external PowerGenerationSubsystem every five minutes to request power allocation, report consumption, and receive generator, solar, and wind status.
missing_requirements.rationale: Integration with the PGS is vital to manage energy resources and ensure continuous power supply.

missing_requirements.description: Internal power distribution and backup power management requirements are missing to support life-critical systems during PGS failures.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: REQ-XXX: The facility shall include a power distribution system with automatic backup power switching capable of maintaining life-critical systems (heating, water, communications, medical equipment) for at least 72 hours during external power failures, with manual override capability.
missing_requirements.rationale: Internal power distribution and backup are critical for life support in case of PGS failure in a remote environment.

missing_requirements.description: No documented emergency response and evacuation procedures for various emergencies including fire, structural damage, and severe weather.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: REQ-XXX: The facility shall provide documented emergency response procedures for medical emergencies, fire, structural damage, and severe weather, including evacuation routes, emergency communication protocols, and equipment locations, accessible to occupants within 30 seconds.
missing_requirements.rationale: Emergency procedures are critical for occupant safety in a remote Antarctic environment with limited rescue capabilities.

missing_requirements.description: Medical emergency management capabilities beyond basic first aid are not defined.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: REQ-XXX: The facility shall provide telemedicine capabilities with high-resolution camera and secure communication to McMurdo Station medical facility, document emergency medical procedures, and allow recording and transmission of vital signs and medical data during emergencies.
missing_requirements.rationale: Given the remote location and mission duration, advanced medical support is essential for occupant safety.

missing_requirements.description: Comprehensive preventive maintenance schedules and spare parts tracking are missing for all equipment.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: REQ-XXX: The facility shall provide preventive maintenance schedules for all equipment (filter replacements, sensor calibration, lubrication, component replacement) with maintenance alerts generated 48 hours before due dates and spare parts inventory tracking.
missing_requirements.rationale: Preventive maintenance is critical to prevent equipment failures that could jeopardize safety and mission success in harsh conditions.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for maintenance scheduling feature and alerts in the DisposalSystem.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: REQ-XXX: The DisposalSystem shall include a maintenance scheduling feature that alerts occupants when routine maintenance is required.
missing_requirements.rationale: Regular maintenance is essential for waste management systems, but there's no requirement for scheduling or alerting.

missing_requirements.description: No scientific data validation and quality control procedures are defined for transmitted research data.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: REQ-XXX: The facility shall perform automated validation of all scientific data (ice core measurements, environmental readings, sample analyses), apply data quality flags and error detection algorithms, and require data review before transmission to the US research team.
missing_requirements.rationale: Data integrity and quality control are essential to ensure research objectives are not compromised by invalid data.

missing_requirements.description: No environmental impact monitoring and reporting requirements to ensure compliance with Antarctic Treaty protocols.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: REQ-XXX: The facility shall continuously monitor environmental parameters (noise levels, emissions, waste generation, energy consumption) and generate weekly environmental impact reports for transmission to NSF.
missing_requirements.rationale: Environmental monitoring is required to demonstrate compliance with Antarctic Treaty Environmental Protection Protocol and mitigate ecological impact.

missing_requirements.description: No requirement for logging all alerts and notifications for troubleshooting and compliance.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: REQ-XXX: The system shall log all alerts, notifications, and system events with timestamps and store logs for at least one year for future analysis.
missing_requirements.rationale: Logging is essential for troubleshooting, audit trails, and regulatory compliance.

missing_requirements.description: No requirement for periodic testing of the WaterStorageSubsystem to ensure reliability.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: REQ-XXX: The WaterStorageSubsystem shall be tested every 24 hours to verify proper functionality, and test results shall be logged.
missing_requirements.rationale: Regular testing ensures system reliability and early detection of malfunctions.

missing_requirements.description: No requirement for user training on the ControlSystem and SmartDevice interfaces.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: REQ-XXX: All occupants shall receive training on using the ControlSystem via SmartDevice and control panels, with training records maintained by the facility.
missing_requirements.rationale: User training is essential for effective system operation and emergency response by authorized personnel.

missing_requirements.description: No HVAC system specifications, capacity, backup heating, or air filtration requirements to support environmental control.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: REQ-XXX: The facility shall include an HVAC system capable of maintaining internal temperature between 65°F and 75°F and relative humidity between 30% and 60% when external temperatures range from -40°F to 80°F, with backup heating capability and air filtration meeting ASHRAE standards.
missing_requirements.rationale: Environmental controls are critical for occupant survival in Antarctic conditions, and no HVAC class or related requirements exist.

domain_model_issues.description: LifeSupportFacility class lacks composition relationships to its constituent subsystems and facility amenities, including DisposalSystem, Storage, EquipmentStorage, IceCoreStorage, Camera, Computer, ElectricityUsageMonitor, MotionSensorSwitch, FuelStorage, Network, Database, ControlSystem, SmartDevice, Shower, Toilet, Sink, WashingMachine, DryingMachine, FirstAidKit, AEDDefibrillator, ExerciseSpace, EatingSpace, Table, Chair, RefrigerationSystem, FreezerSystem, Stove, Bed, and MobileCot, and does not enforce quantity constraints (e.g., 5 beds, 1 mobile cot, 2 sinks, 1 table, 5 chairs).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Introduce composition relationships between LifeSupportFacility and each required subsystem and amenity, specifying correct cardinalities (e.g., LifeSupportFacility *-- Bed [5], *-- MobileCot [1], etc.).

domain_model_issues.description: MonitoringDevice has composition relationships with each water subsystem, which may lead to redundant devices instead of a centralized monitoring approach.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Replace composition with association or clarify if each subsystem requires its own MonitoringDevice to avoid redundancy.

domain_model_issues.description: PowerGenerationSubsystem class is missing despite requirements for monitoring power generation, scheduling tests every 8 hours, and notifying failures.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add PowerGenerationSubsystem class with monitoring capabilities, scheduledTest() every 8 hours, and failure notification methods.

domain_model_issues.description: HVACSystem class is missing despite requirements for climate control monitoring, testing heating equipment every 8 hours, and sending failure notifications within 1 minute.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add HVACSystem class with methods for scheduled testing and failure notifications.

domain_model_issues.description: FireDetectionSystem class is missing despite requirements for hourly testing of fire detection equipment and sending failure notifications within 1 minute.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add FireDetectionSystem class with testing methods and failure notification capabilities.

domain_model_issues.description: CarbonMonoxideDetectionSystem class is missing despite requirements for hourly testing of CO detection equipment and sending failure notifications within 1 minute.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add CarbonMonoxideDetectionSystem class with testing and notification methods.

domain_model_issues.description: ElectricalSystem class is missing despite requirements for testing electrical equipment every 8 hours.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add ElectricalSystem class with testing and monitoring methods.

domain_model_issues.description: NotificationSystem class is missing despite requirements for sending failure notifications within 1 minute for heating, climate control, water filtration, and fire/CO systems.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add NotificationSystem class with timed alert methods for different failure types.

domain_model_issues.description: EncryptionSystem class is missing despite requirements for encrypted communications with the US research lab and encrypted data storage.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add EncryptionSystem class with methods for encrypting communications and storing data securely.

domain_model_issues.description: BuiltInTestSystem class is missing despite requirements for scheduled self-tests of power, heating, water filtration, electrical, fire detection, and CO detection systems.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add BuiltInTestSystem class with runBuiltInTest() methods to schedule and execute tests for all critical subsystems.

domain_model_issues.description: No sensor classes are defined for monitoring critical equipment such as power generation, HVAC, or drilling equipment.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add specialized sensor classes (e.g., PowerSensor, HVACSensor, DrillingEquipmentSensor) to capture equipment health data.

domain_model_issues.description: DisposalSystem class lacks composition within LifeSupportFacility, does not include attributes for operating temperature range or weather resistance, and has no methods to handle extreme weather or regulatory compliance.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add composition LifeSupportFacility *-- DisposalSystem, attributes operatingTemperatureRange:TemperatureRange and weatherResistanceRating:String, and methods handleExtremeWeather() and checkCompliance().

domain_model_issues.description: WaterRecyclingSubsystem.filterWater method lacks parameters and return type, missing attributes for throughput capacity, standards compliance, and water quality metrics, and is not composed within LifeSupportFacility.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Define filterWater(volume:double, type:WaterType):Water (or FilterResult), add attributes throughputCapacity:double, standardsCompliance:String, waterQualityMetrics (e.g., pH:double, contaminants:List), and compose within LifeSupportFacility.

domain_model_issues.description: WaterStorageSubsystem lacks attributes for total volume, potable, black, and gray water capacities, uses a weakly typed String[] for water types, and is not composed within LifeSupportFacility or equipped to handle extreme weather.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add attributes totalVolume:double, potableCapacity:double, blackCapacity:double, grayCapacity:double; replace waterTypes:String[] with an enum WaterType; add method handleExtremeWeather(); and compose within LifeSupportFacility.

domain_model_issues.description: Storage class lacks nonPerishableVolume, perishableVolume, location attributes, and has no links to RefrigerationSystem or FreezerSystem for temperature-controlled storage.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add attributes nonPerishableVolume:double, perishableVolume:double, location:String; compose Storage within LifeSupportFacility and associate it with RefrigerationSystem and FreezerSystem.

domain_model_issues.description: IceCoreStorage class is missing temperatureRange attribute to enforce -40°F to 20°F, maxCapacity for 20 cores, and currentCount.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add attributes temperatureRange:TemperatureRange, maxCapacity:int, and currentCount:int to IceCoreStorage.

domain_model_issues.description: RefrigerationSystem class lacks a refrigerationCapacity attribute to ensure at least 48 cubic feet of cooling space.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add attribute refrigerationCapacity:double (in cubic feet) to RefrigerationSystem.

domain_model_issues.description: FreezerSystem class lacks a freezerCapacity attribute to ensure at least 19.5 cubic feet of freezing space.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add attribute freezerCapacity:double (in cubic feet) to FreezerSystem.

domain_model_issues.description: Stove class does not specify the number of burners required for operation.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add attribute burnerCount:int and set minimum value to 2.

domain_model_issues.description: SecuritySystem class is missing despite requirements for physical access control and locked control panels.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add SecuritySystem class with methods for locking panels and enforcing access control.

domain_model_issues.description: MaintenanceSystem class is missing despite requirements for maintenance reminders and filter/equipment restocking schedules.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add MaintenanceSystem class with scheduling and notification methods for maintenance tasks.

domain_model_issues.description: Database class is not composed within LifeSupportFacility and lacks associations to Storage and CloudStorage for data persistence.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add composition LifeSupportFacility *-- Database and associations between Database and Storage, as well as Database and CloudStorage.

domain_model_issues.description: MotionSensorSwitch class is not composed within LifeSupportFacility and there is no Outlet class to represent its power connection.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Create an Outlet class, add composition LifeSupportFacility *-- MotionSensorSwitch, and associate MotionSensorSwitch with Outlet.

domain_model_issues.description: FuelStorage class is not composed within LifeSupportFacility and lacks a complianceStandard attribute for SPCC regulations.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add composition LifeSupportFacility *-- FuelStorage and attribute complianceStandard:String (e.g., '40 CFR Part 112').

domain_model_issues.description: Network class is not composed within LifeSupportFacility, lacks attributes averageWifiSpeed and encryptionEnabled, and has no methods to encrypt data or monitor Wi-Fi performance.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add composition LifeSupportFacility *-- Network, add attributes averageWifiSpeed:int and encryptionEnabled:boolean, and implement methods encryptData() and monitorWiFiSpeed().

domain_model_issues.description: ControlSystem class lacks relationships to the systems it controls (e.g., HVACSystem, WaterRecyclingSubsystem), does not include a ControlPanel subclass with lock/unlock functionality, lacks methods for authentication and smart device control, and missing encryptionEnabled attribute.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add associations between ControlSystem and controlled subsystems, introduce a ControlPanel class with locked:boolean and methods lockPanel(), unlockPanel(), add methods authenticateUser(), monitorControlSystem(), sendControlCommand(), and attribute encryptionEnabled on ControlSystem.

domain_model_issues.description: SmartDevice class lacks methods to monitor or send commands to the ControlSystem and other subsystems.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add methods monitorControlSystem():Status and sendControlCommand(command:String):void, and associate SmartDevice with ControlSystem.

domain_model_issues.description: PotableWaterSystem class has no method to generate potable water, no standardsCompliance attribute, and lacks visible pH display functionality.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add generatePotableWater():Water method, attribute standardsCompliance:String, and pHDisplay/displayPHLevel():void to PotableWaterSystem.

domain_model_issues.description: FireSuppressionSystem class is not composed within LifeSupportFacility, lacks built-in test operations, and has no detection capabilities or integration with MonitoringDevice.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add composition LifeSupportFacility *-- FireSuppressionSystem, implement builtInTest():TestResult, and include detection methods or integrate FireDetectionSystem functionality.

domain_model_issues.description: Camera class is not composed within LifeSupportFacility.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add composition LifeSupportFacility *-- Camera [1].

domain_model_issues.description: Computer class is not linked to LifeSupportFacility with the required cardinality of 3 units and lacks an encryptionEnabled attribute.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add composition LifeSupportFacility *-- Computer [3] and add attribute encryptionEnabled:boolean.

domain_model_issues.description: CloudStorage class has no associations to ResearchTeam or LifeSupportFacility and lacks an encryptionEnabled attribute.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add association ResearchTeam *-- CloudStorage and composition or association LifeSupportFacility -- CloudStorage, and add attribute encryptionEnabled:boolean.

domain_model_issues.description: ResearchTeam class is missing an association to CloudStorage for cloud-based data storage.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add association ResearchTeam -- CloudStorage.

domain_model_issues.description: MonitoringDevice class lacks attributes to store water quality metrics (e.g., contaminationLevels, pH) and methods to test equipment such as testWaterFiltration() and testFireDetection().
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add attributes for water quality metrics and implement methods testWaterFiltration(), testFireDetection().

domain_model_issues.description: ExerciseSpace class is missing a minimumArea attribute to enforce at least 100 square feet of space.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add minimumArea:double attribute to ExerciseSpace with a value of 100.

domain_model_issues.description: EatingSpace class is missing a minimumArea attribute to enforce at least 100 square feet of space.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add minimumArea:double attribute to EatingSpace with a value of 100.

domain_model_issues.description: ElectricityUsageMonitor class is missing a generateDailyReport method for daily energy consumption reporting.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add generateDailyReport():EnergyReport method to ElectricityUsageMonitor.

domain_model_issues.description: Generic system methods lack parameters and do not capture specific operational details.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add appropriate parameters to methods such as store(waterType, amount) and filterWater(inputSource, outputTarget).

domain_model_issues.description: Class naming patterns are inconsistent (e.g., using 'Storage' vs. specific storage types).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Establish consistent naming conventions and rename classes accordingly (e.g., GeneralStorage, DataTransmissionComputer).

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The water recycling subsystem shall filter water in accordance with safety water standards defined by regulatory bodies.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: Include metadata fields (unique identifier, priority, rationale, source, status, version, dependencies, type, quality attributes) for traceability; specify regulatory standards by referencing EPA Safe Drinking Water Act (40 CFR 141) and WHO drinking water guidelines; define filtration efficiency target of 99.9% removal of contaminants, verified via quarterly water quality tests; acceptance criteria: water quality test results must meet all specified standards.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement lacks metadata for traceability and prioritization; missing specific standards, measurable efficiency targets, and test criteria undermines testability and clarity.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The water recycling subsystem shall include a monitoring device that alerts the LSF when the filtering system requires change or maintenance, with data retrieved via a dedicated application.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: Add metadata fields (unique identifier, priority, rationale, source, status, version, dependencies, type, quality attributes); define alert trigger conditions (e.g., filter capacity below 80% or scheduled maintenance), include both visual and audible alerts; set acceptance criteria: alerts must be generated within 30 seconds; ensure real-time data retrieval via a dedicated iOS and Android application.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Ensures requirement traceability and prioritization; specifying trigger thresholds, alert methods, and timing makes the behavior verifiable and testable.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The water storage subsystem shall store potable, black, and gray water for occupants, meeting capacity requirements as defined in the Water Storage Tank SRS.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: Include metadata fields (unique identifier, priority, rationale, source, status, version, dependencies, type, quality attributes); specify minimum storage capacities (e.g., potable 500 gallons, black water 200 gallons, grey water 300 gallons) for up to 6 occupants for 30 days as per Water Storage Tank SRS v2.1; define acceptance criteria: each tank must meet or exceed specified volumes.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Requires metadata for traceability; without specific volume values and version reference, it's unclear and not testable; explicit criteria ensure capacity needs are met.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The water storage subsystem shall include a monitoring device that communicates water quality and contamination levels to the LSF.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: Add metadata fields (unique identifier, priority, rationale, source, status, version, dependencies, type, quality attributes); define monitored parameters (pH, turbidity, chlorine residual, bacterial count); specify measurement frequency (every 15 minutes) and contamination alert threshold based on EPA standards; acceptance criteria: alerts shall be generated within 5 minutes of threshold breach.
requirement_completeness.rationale: The requirement lacks metadata; without specified quality parameters, measurement frequency, and alert timing, it's not testable; adding these details ensures clarity and verifiability.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: Process waste. The facility shall implement a disposal system for trash and waste that remains effective under extreme weather conditions.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: Include metadata fields (unique identifier, priority, rationale, source, status, version, dependencies, type, quality attributes); specify waste processing capacity (e.g., 50 lbs solid waste per day); define operational environmental range (temperatures -40°F to 80°F, wind speeds up to 100 mph); acceptance criteria: system shall process specified waste capacity continuously for 24 hours without failure under defined conditions and comply with Antarctic environmental protection.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Lacks metadata and quantifiable environmental and performance metrics; explicit capacity, environmental limits, and test duration are needed for testability and reliability.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: Store non-perishable and perishable goods. Non-perishable items shall be stored in a clean, dry environment near the kitchen, while perishable goods require adequate refrigeration/freezing capacity for extended periods.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: Add metadata fields (unique identifier, priority, rationale, source, status, version, dependencies, type, quality attributes); specify non-perishable storage requirements (minimum 200 cu ft, humidity <50%, temperature 32-80°F, within 50 ft of kitchen) and perishable storage (refrigeration: 48 cu ft at 32-40°F; freezer: 19.5 cu ft at 0-10°F for up to 90 days); acceptance criteria: temperature logs shall demonstrate compliance over defined periods.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Without metadata, capacity, environmental, and duration specifics, the requirement is ambiguous and not verifiable; detailed metrics ensure operational clarity and testability.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: Monitor the health of critical equipment via a network of wired or wireless sensors covering systems such as power generation, HVAC, water purification, waste management, and drilling.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: Include metadata fields (unique identifier, priority, rationale, source, status, version, dependencies, type, quality attributes); deploy at least 50 wired or wireless sensors with 99.9% uptime covering critical systems; specify update frequency (every 60 seconds) and fault detection within 5 seconds; acceptance criteria: sensor network must meet uptime and latency requirements.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Missing metadata and measurable uptime, sensor count, frequency, and fault detection metrics hinder verification; explicit criteria ensure operational performance.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: Provide sufficient storage and maintenance space for expedition and drilling equipment, including heavy machinery, transport vehicles, and maintenance tools, with appropriate environmental controls.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: Add metadata fields (unique identifier, priority, rationale, source, status, version, dependencies, type, quality attributes); specify minimum storage/maintenance area (e.g., 2000 sq ft heated at 40-80°F); include overhead crane capacity (5-ton), space allocation for 2 snowmobiles and drilling rig components, and a dedicated maintenance workshop with ventilation; acceptance criteria: space and environmental controls meet specified dimensions and capacities.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Lacks metadata, quantified space, equipment capacity, and environmental parameters; clear specifications enable validation and operational readiness.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: Store ice cores. The facility shall be capable of simultaneously storing 20 ice cores at temperatures maintained between -40°F and 20°F.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: Include metadata fields (unique identifier, priority, rationale, source, status, version, dependencies, type, quality attributes); define ice core dimensions (e.g., up to 10 ft length, 4 in diameter); specify temperature range (-40°F to 20°F) with variance ±2°F; continuous monitoring with 5-minute data logging; acceptance criteria: logs shall confirm temperature stability within tolerance.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Without metadata and precise dimensional, tolerance, and monitoring requirements, it's not verifiable; explicit criteria ensure quality core preservation.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: Support scientific data exchange with the US research lab through encrypted transmission.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: Add metadata fields (unique identifier, priority, rationale, source, status, version, dependencies, type, quality attributes); support bi-directional scientific data exchange over AES-256 encryption, capable of transferring up to 1 GB files with 99.9% reliability and latency ≤5 seconds for priority communications; acceptance criteria: all transmissions must pass encryption validation and performance tests.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Missing metadata and specific encryption standards, performance, and reliability criteria; detailed metrics ensure security and data exchange performance.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The LSF shall contain at least one radio for communication with McMurdo Station, which must operate on battery backup, feature a hand-crank function, and utilize solar power.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: Include metadata fields (unique identifier, priority, rationale, source, status, version, dependencies, type, quality attributes); specify HF/VHF radio system operating on AC power with 72-hour battery backup, manual hand-crank charging (10 minutes crank for 1 hour operation), and 50 W solar panel charging; maintain at least 500-mile communication range in all weather; acceptance criteria: radio must meet backup, charging, and range specifications.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Lacks metadata and quantitative performance metrics for reliability; explicit specifications ensure communication capability under all conditions.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The LSF shall contain at least one camera for video conferencing.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: Add metadata fields (unique identifier, priority, rationale, source, status, version, dependencies, type, quality attributes); supply HD camera (1080p at ≥30 fps) with integrated microphone, supporting simultaneous video conferencing for up to 8 participants; ensure compatibility with H.323 and SIP protocols; acceptance criteria: video calls maintain ≥95% uptime.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Requirement lacks metadata and technical quality, capacity, and protocol details; clear specifications enable quality conferencing performance.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The LSF shall contain at least three computers to support data transmission, with data storage maintained on an encrypted server.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: Include metadata fields (unique identifier, priority, rationale, source, status, version, dependencies, type, quality attributes); procure three computers with Intel i5 processors, ≥16 GB RAM, and ≥1 TB SSD for data transmission at ≥25 Mbps; maintain data on AES-256 encrypted server with ≥10 TB capacity and daily automated backups; acceptance criteria: data retrieval latency <500 ms.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Missing metadata and detailed hardware, performance, encryption, storage, and backup requirements; precise criteria ensure efficient and secure data support.

reasoning.domain_model: I consolidated duplicate classes across the three models (e.g., LSF and Facility into LifeSupportFacility), merged method and attribute details (standardizing filterWater over filter vs filterWater), and retained unique domain elements from each source (e.g., PotableWaterSystem for pH display, DisposalSystem, general Storage classes, accommodations, and infrastructure like Network and Database). Relationships and multiplicities were carried forward or resolved by unifying MonitoringSystem to MonitoringDevice. All classes, methods, attributes, and associations now form a complete and consistent domain model, and the PlantUML diagram reflects these elements and connections.
reasoning.analysis:
Analysis aggregated using openai with specialized component processing:
- requirement_completeness: Aggregated assessments from Claude, OpenAI, and DeepSeek. For each requirement, the minimum completeness score (20.0) was selected to maintain a conservative rating. Missing elements were merged from all sources (duplicates removed) to ensure a comprehensive list. The most detailed suggested improvements and rationales were preserved to address all identified deficiencies, ensuring clarity and testability of each requirement.
- requirement_issues: No requirement issues found in any analysis
- missing_requirements: After comparing the three source analyses, all 31 missing requirements (MR1–MR31) were identical and consistent across sources. This consolidated list preserves each unique requirement with the most detailed description, suggested text, and rationale provided.
- domain_model_issues: Combined issues from three sources by grouping missing subsystem classes, incomplete class definitions, relationship design flaws, attribute omissions, and method gaps into a unified list. Similar entries were merged with the most detailed descriptions and fixes, severity levels standardized to MUST FIX/SHOULD FIX/SUGGESTION, and affected requirement IDs aggregated to ensure complete coverage.
